{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "project-rulebook-api-testing",
		"name": "Project Rulebook API Testing Collection",
		"description": "Comprehensive API testing collection for the Project Rulebook Vapor backend.\n\n## Quick Start\n1. Import this collection into Postman or RapidAPI\n2. Set environment variables: `base_url`, `admin_email`, `admin_password`\n3. Run the \"Authentication → Admin Login\" request first\n4. Test other endpoints with the stored JWT tokens\n\n## Admin Credentials (Seeded)\n- Email: root@localhost.com\n- Password: ChangeMe1\n\n## Available Endpoints\n- **Authentication** (6 endpoints): login, signup, Apple Sign-In, password reset, logout, token refresh\n- **User Management** (4 endpoints): profile view/update/delete, admin user listing\n- **Rules Generation** (2 endpoints): game box image analysis, rules summary generation\n- **Cache Administration** (6 endpoints): stats, health checks, Redis monitoring, entry management, cleanup\n\n## Total Endpoints: 18 API endpoints\n\n## Authentication Requirements\n- **Public**: signup, login, Apple Sign-In, password reset\n- **User Protected**: logout, profile management, rules generation\n- **Admin Only**: user listing, all cache administration endpoints",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Authentication",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Admin Login",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Store tokens from login response",
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    // Tokens are nested in response.token",
									"    pm.environment.set('access_token', response.token.accessToken);",
									"    pm.environment.set('refresh_token', response.token.refreshToken);",
									"    console.log('✅ Login successful - tokens stored');",
									"    console.log('👤 User:', response.user.email, '(Admin:', response.user.isAdmin, ')');",
									"} else {",
									"    console.log('❌ Login failed:', pm.response.text());",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{admin_email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{admin_password}}\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/sign-in",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "auth", "sign-in"]
						},
						"description": "Login with admin credentials to get JWT tokens for protected endpoints."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "User Signup",
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"test@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"TestPassword123\",\n  \"firstName\": \"Test\",\n  \"lastName\": \"User\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/sign-up",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "auth", "sign-up"]
						},
						"description": "Register a new user account."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Apple Sign-In",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Store tokens from Apple auth response",
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.environment.set('access_token', response.token.accessToken);",
									"    pm.environment.set('refresh_token', response.token.refreshToken);",
									"    console.log('✅ Apple Sign-In successful - tokens stored');",
									"    console.log('👤 User:', response.user.email);",
									"} else {",
									"    console.log('❌ Apple Sign-In failed:', pm.response.text());",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n  \"identityToken\": \"eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\",\n  \"authorizationCode\": \"c1234567890abcdef\",\n  \"user\": {\n    \"firstName\": \"John\",\n    \"lastName\": \"Doe\",\n    \"email\": \"john.doe@privaterelay.appleid.com\"\n  }\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/apple-auth",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "auth", "apple-auth"]
						},
						"description": "Authenticate using Apple Sign-In credentials.\n\n**Rate Limited**: Yes\n\n**Request Format**:\n- identityToken: JWT from Apple Sign-In\n- authorizationCode: Authorization code from Apple\n- user: User information (only provided on first sign-in)\n\n**Expected Response**:\n```json\n{\n  \"token\": {\n    \"accessToken\": \"jwt_access_token\",\n    \"refreshToken\": \"jwt_refresh_token\"\n  },\n  \"user\": {\n    \"id\": \"uuid\",\n    \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n    \"firstName\": \"John\",\n    \"lastName\": \"Doe\",\n    \"isAdmin\": false\n  }\n}\n```"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Refresh Token",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Update access token from refresh response",
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    // Update both tokens from response",
									"    pm.environment.set('access_token', response.accessToken);",
									"    pm.environment.set('refresh_token', response.refreshToken);",
									"    console.log('✅ Token refreshed successfully');",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n  \"refreshToken\": \"{{refresh_token}}\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/refresh",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "auth", "refresh"]
						},
						"description": "Refresh access token using the refresh token."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Request Password Reset",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Validate password reset response",
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    console.log('✅ Password reset email sent successfully');",
									"} else {",
									"    console.log('❌ Password reset failed:', pm.response.text());",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/reset-password",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "auth", "reset-password"]
						},
						"description": "Request a password reset email for the specified user.\n\n**Rate Limited**: Yes - prevents email spam\n\n**Expected Response**:\n```json\n{\n  \"message\": \"Password reset email sent if account exists\"\n}\n```\n\n**Note**: For security, this endpoint always returns success even if the email doesn't exist."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Logout",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Clear stored tokens on successful logout",
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    pm.environment.unset('access_token');",
									"    pm.environment.unset('refresh_token');",
									"    console.log('✅ Logged out successfully - tokens cleared');",
									"} else {",
									"    console.log('❌ Logout failed:', pm.response.text());",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{access_token}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/logout",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "auth", "logout"]
						},
						"description": "Logout user and invalidate all refresh tokens.\n\n**Requires**: Bearer token authentication\n\n**Expected Response**:\n```json\n{\n  \"message\": \"Logout successful\"\n}\n```\n\n**Security**: Invalidates all refresh tokens for the user, forcing re-authentication on all devices."
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "Authentication endpoints for login, signup, Apple Sign-In, password reset, and token management."
		},
		{
			"name": "User Management",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Get Current User Profile",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Validate user profile response",
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.test('User has email', () => {",
									"        pm.expect(response).to.have.property('email');",
									"    });",
									"    pm.test('User has ID', () => {",
									"        pm.expect(response).to.have.property('id');",
									"    });",
									"    console.log('👤 User Profile:');",
									"    console.log('   Email:', response.email);",
									"    console.log('   Name:', response.firstName, response.lastName);",
									"    console.log('   Admin:', response.isAdmin);",
									"    console.log('   Verified:', response.emailVerified);",
									"} else {",
									"    console.log('❌ Failed to get user profile:', pm.response.text());",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{access_token}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/user/me",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "user", "me"]
						},
						"description": "Get current user's profile information.\n\n**Requires**: Bearer token authentication\n\n**Expected Response**:\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"uuid\",\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n  \"firstName\": \"John\",\n  \"lastName\": \"Doe\",\n  \"isAdmin\": false,\n  \"emailVerified\": true,\n  \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-01T12:00:00Z\"\n}\n```"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Update User Profile",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Validate profile update response",
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    console.log('✅ Profile updated successfully');",
									"    console.log('   Updated Name:', response.firstName, response.lastName);",
									"} else {",
									"    console.log('❌ Profile update failed:', pm.response.text());",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "PATCH",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{access_token}}",
								"type": "text"
							},
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n  \"firstName\": \"Updated First Name\",\n  \"lastName\": \"Updated Last Name\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/user/update",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "user", "update"]
						},
						"description": "Update current user's profile information.\n\n**Requires**: Bearer token authentication\n\n**Request Body** (all fields optional):\n```json\n{\n  \"firstName\": \"string\",\n  \"lastName\": \"string\"\n}\n```\n\n**Expected Response**: Updated user profile data"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Delete User Account",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Validate account deletion response",
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    // Clear tokens since account is deleted",
									"    pm.environment.unset('access_token');",
									"    pm.environment.unset('refresh_token');",
									"    console.log('✅ Account deleted successfully - tokens cleared');",
									"    console.log('⚠️ User account has been permanently removed');",
									"} else {",
									"    console.log('❌ Account deletion failed:', pm.response.text());",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						},
						{
							"listen": "prerequest",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Confirm destructive action",
									"console.log('⚠️ WARNING: This will permanently delete the user account!');"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "DELETE",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{access_token}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/user/delete",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "user", "delete"]
						},
						"description": "⚠️ **DESTRUCTIVE ACTION** ⚠️\n\nPermanently delete the current user account.\n\n**Requires**: Bearer token authentication\n\n**Security**: This action cannot be undone. All user data will be permanently removed.\n\n**Expected Response**: HTTP 200 OK"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "List All Users (Admin)",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Validate user list response",
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    if (Array.isArray(response)) {",
									"        console.log('👥 Total users found:', response.length);",
									"        response.forEach((user, index) => {",
									"            console.log(`   ${index + 1}. ${user.email} (${user.firstName} ${user.lastName}) - Admin: ${user.isAdmin}`);",
									"        });",
									"    } else {",
									"        console.log('📋 User data:', response);",
									"    }",
									"} else {",
									"    console.log('❌ Failed to get user list:', pm.response.text());",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{access_token}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/user/list",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "user", "list"]
						},
						"description": "List all registered users (admin only).\n\n**Requires**: Admin Bearer token authentication\n\n**Authorization**: Admin users only\n\n**Expected Response**:\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"id\": \"uuid\",\n    \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n    \"firstName\": \"John\",\n    \"lastName\": \"Doe\",\n    \"isAdmin\": false,\n    \"emailVerified\": true,\n    \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-01T12:00:00Z\"\n  }\n]\n```"
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "User management endpoints for profile operations and admin user listing."
		},
		{
			"name": "Rules Generation",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Analyze Game Box Image",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "prerequest",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Note: This endpoint now accepts raw binary image data",
									"// You can directly upload image files",
									"console.log('📸 Ready to accept image files directly');",
									"console.log('🖼️ Supported formats: PNG, JPG, JPEG, GIF');"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						},
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Validate response structure",
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.test('Response has guessed title', () => {",
									"        pm.expect(response).to.have.property('guessedTitle');",
									"    });",
									"    pm.test('Response has confidence score', () => {",
									"        pm.expect(response).to.have.property('confidence');",
									"        pm.expect(response.confidence).to.be.a('number');",
									"    });",
									"    console.log('🎲 Game detected:', response.guessedTitle, '(confidence:', response.confidence + '%)');",
									"} else {",
									"    console.log('❌ Error:', pm.response.text());",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/octet-stream"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "file",
							"file": {
								"src": ""
							}
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/rules-generation/game-box-analysis",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "rules-generation", "game-box-analysis"]
						},
						"description": "Analyze a game box image to identify the board game using AI.\n\n**IMPORTANT**: This endpoint now accepts raw binary image data directly.\n\n**Request Format**:\n- Body: Binary image data\n- Content-Type: `application/octet-stream`\n- Method: POST\n\n**How to use**:\n1. **Postman**: Select Body → binary → Choose File\n2. **cURL**: `curl -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/octet-stream\" --data-binary @your-image.png {url}`\n3. **Code**: Send raw image bytes in request body\n\n**Supported Formats**: PNG, JPG, JPEG, GIF\n\n**Rate Limited**: 50 requests/hour (dev), 3 requests/hour (prod)\n\n**Expected Response**:\n```json\n{\n  \"guessedTitle\": \"Monopoly\",\n  \"confidence\": 95,\n  \"alternativeTitles\": [\"Monopoly Classic\"],\n  \"keywordsDetected\": [\"Parker Brothers\", \"Real Estate Game\"],\n  \"notes\": \"Clear title visibility, high confidence match\"\n}\n```"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Generate Rules Summary",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Validate response structure",
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.test('Response has game title', () => {",
									"        pm.expect(response).to.have.property('title');",
									"    });",
									"    pm.test('Response has setup instructions', () => {",
									"        pm.expect(response).to.have.property('initialSetup');",
									"        pm.expect(response.initialSetup).to.be.an('array');",
									"    });",
									"    pm.test('Response has win condition', () => {",
									"        pm.expect(response).to.have.property('winCondition');",
									"    });",
									"    console.log('📋 Rules generated for:', response.title);",
									"    console.log('👥 Players:', response.playerCount);",
									"    console.log('⏱️ Play time:', response.playTime);",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n  \"gameTitle\": \"Monopoly\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/rules-generation/rules-summary",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "rules-generation", "rules-summary"]
						},
						"description": "Generate comprehensive rules summary for a board game.\n\n**Rate Limited**: 10 requests per hour (development), 5 requests per hour (production)\n\n**Expected Response**:\n```json\n{\n  \"title\": \"Monopoly\",\n  \"playerCount\": \"2-8 players\",\n  \"playTime\": \"60-180 minutes\",\n  \"summary\": \"Real estate trading game...\",\n  \"initialSetup\": [\"Place board in center\", \"Each player chooses token\"],\n  \"firstRoundGuide\": [\"Roll dice to move\", \"Buy properties you land on\"],\n  \"winCondition\": \"Be the last player with money when others go bankrupt\",\n  \"deepDive\": [\"Advanced strategy tips...\"],\n  \"resources\": {\n    \"videoLinks\": [\"https://youtube.com/watch?v=example\"],\n    \"webLinks\": [\"https://boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/1406/monopoly\"]\n  },\n  \"confidence\": 90,\n  \"notes\": \"Classic game with well-documented rules\"\n}\n```"
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "AI-powered game rules generation endpoints for image analysis and rules summary."
		},
		{
			"name": "Cache Administration",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Cache Statistics",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Validate cache stats response",
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.test('Has cache statistics', () => {",
									"        pm.expect(response).to.have.property('hits');",
									"        pm.expect(response).to.have.property('misses');",
									"        pm.expect(response).to.have.property('entryCount');",
									"    });",
									"    console.log('📊 Cache Stats:');",
									"    console.log('   Hits:', response.hits);",
									"    console.log('   Misses:', response.misses);",
									"    console.log('   Hit Ratio:', response.hitRatio + '%');",
									"    console.log('   Entries:', response.entryCount + '/' + response.maxEntries);",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{access_token}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
